<div id="header--case-study-3">
    <div class="flex header--case-study">
        <div class="flex flex--column gap--sm flex-1 flex--justify-center flex--grow-1">
            <h2>Social media and echo chambers</h2>
            <p>Social media has enabled news to travel far and fast, and has given a voice and platform to many people to share their point of view. Anyone can find, share or create information instantly and broadcast it to the masses.</p>
            <p>Social media can also enable <span class="tooltip-trigger jsTooltip" data-tooltip-content="#tooltip3_content">echo chambers</span> where users are continuously fed more information that supports their <span class="tooltip-trigger jsTooltip" data-tooltip-content="#tooltip4_content">preconceptions</span>, whether this information is real or made-up.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-1 flex--align-end">
            <img src="/badge-assets/digital-ethics/_global/svg/illustrations/illustration--cases-study-social-media.svg" alt="" />
        </div>
    </div>
</div>